      "description": "Common Weakness Enumeration",
      "weight": 100,
      "data": {
        "official_name": "Common Weakness Enumeration",
        "common_name": "CWE",
        "alternate_names": null,
        "description": "The canonical software and hardware weakness taxonomy, operated by MITRE.",
        "notes": "Hierarchical taxonomy with three structural levels: views (organize weaknesses by perspective, e.g., CWE-1000 Research Concepts), categories (group related weaknesses, e.g., CWE-19 Data Processing Errors), and weaknesses (specific flaw types, e.g., CWE-79 XSS). Over 900 weakness entries. Referenced by CVE, NVD, and virtually all vulnerability databases.\n\nAI/ML weaknesses added in the CWE-1400 series: CWE-1426 (Improper Validation of Generative AI Output), CWE-1427 (Improper Neutralization of Input for LLM Prompting), CWE-1434 (Insecure ML Model Inference Parameters).\n\nAll CWE IDs (views, categories, and weaknesses) use the same numeric format and the same URL template. The CWE number space is shared — no collisions between types. Updated regularly with community contributions.",
        "urls": [
          {
            "type": "website",
            "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org"
          },
          {
            "type": "docs",
            "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/index.html",
            "note": "CWE data index — links to XML, CSV, and PDF downloads"
          },
          {
            "type": "bulk_data",
            "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/xml/cwec_latest.xml.zip",
            "format": "xml",
            "note": "Full CWE list in XML format (zipped)"
          }
        ],
        "examples": [
          "CWE-79",
          "CWE-89",
          "CWE-22",
          "CWE-78",
          "CWE-1427"
        ],
